This paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their optimization, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the concept of relay nodes becoming obsolete in the Moving Sink scheme, which relates to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper proposes a new scheme for sink mobility, which involves dividing the field into small squares, which is a form of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of linear programming equations to support the model, which falls under Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Information Theory (cs.IT).
